Heat oven to 350 degrees F. Unroll dough into 2 long rectangles. Place in ungreased 13x9-inch pan; press over bottom to form crust. Firmly press perforations to seal. Beat cream cheese in medium bowl until light and fluffy. Add sour cream and eggs; beat well. Add crabmeat, 1/2 cup of the cheese, onions, salt and pepper; mix well. Spoon and spread over dough in pan. Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese. Bake at 350 degrees F for 35 to 40 minutes or until center is set and edges are golden brown. Cool 10 minutes. Cut into squares.